p after the holiday season - we hope you had a good one :-)


--- Featured ---

# Results of the 2012 DailyJS JavaScript Developer Survey
http://dailyjs.com/2012/12/24/javascript-survey-results/

With 2747 responses there are lots of interesting trends to see. 85% of re=
spondents dig semicolons, Jasmine is the most popular testing library, and=
 RequireJS is the most popular module loading system.

# Web Platform Doc Sprint Berlin, February 8=E2=80=939, 2013
http://lanyrd.com/2013/wpds/

Join like-minded contributors and help to document the web platform and im=
prove the WebPlatform.org user experience.

# ScriptCraft: Program Minecraft in JavaScript
http://walterhiggins.net/blog/ScriptCraft

Eases the cumbersome edit/compile/reobfuscate/rejar cycle of developing a=
 Minecraft mod, by letting you write mods in JavaScript.

# Douglas Crockford: =E2=80=9CJava was a colossal failure... JavaScript is=
 succeeding because it works.=E2=80=9D [Interview]
http://jaxenter.com/douglas-crockford-java-was-a-colossal-failure-javascri=
pt-is-succeeding-because-it-works-45928.html


--- From our Sponsor ---

# HTML5DevConf April 1-3: Call for Speakers and Pre-Sale Tickets
http://html5devconf.com/

Presale tickets are open for HTML5DevConf, the world's largest JavaScript=
 and HTML5 developer conference. We honor our San Francisco grassroots tra=
dition with a limited number of presale tickets at $65; these will be gone=
 within days. Interested, accomplished speakers are invited to apply by Ja=
n 31.


--- Reading ---

# Revisiting JavaScript Objects
http://www.laktek.com/2012/12/29/revisiting-javascript-objects/

Lakshan Perera explains ECMAScript 5 features related to objects: data and=
 accessor properties, property descriptors, tamper-proofing objects, etc.

# JavaScript Terminology: The Two 'Prototype's
http://www.2ality.com/2013/01/two-prototypes.html

# Dashing D3.js: Tutorials, Screencasts, and a Newsletter
http://www.dashingd3js.com/

An excellent set of resources for the popular data visualization framework=
, D3.js.

# Conditional Loading of Resources with Media Queries
http://christianheilmann.com/2012/12/19/conditional-loading-of-resources-w=
ith-mediaqueries/

Christian Heilmann experiments with the idea of using media queries as a b=
asis for loading specific page assets rather than just styling them.

# Asynchronous Error Handling in JavaScript
http://ruben.verborgh.org/blog/2012/12/31/asynchronous-error-handling-in-j=
avascript/

The lessons we=E2=80=99ve been taught as programmers to nicely throw and c=
atch excep=C2=ADtions don=E2=80=99t apply in asynchronous environments.

# Implementing Push Technology Using Server-Sent Events
http://jspro.com/apis/implementing-push-technology-using-server-sent-event=
s/

Server-Sent Events allow servers to notify clients. They are an alternativ=
e to WebSockets for many tasks.

# JSComplexity.org: Measure the Complexity of Your Source Code
http://jscomplexity.org/

The site supports four metrics: lines of code, cyclomatic complexity, Hals=
tead complexity measures and the maintainability index. It computes those=
 metrics via the complexityReport.js library.

# Building JavaScript Projects with Grunt
http://ruudud.github.com/2012/12/22/grunt/

Pre-compile templates, minify and concatenate files, etc.

# 10 Vital Aspects of Building a Node.js Application
https://engineering.gosquared.com/10-vital-aspects-of-building-a-node-js-a=
pplication

# Session-based Authorization with Socket.IO
http://howtonode.org/socket-io-auth

# Remy Sharp=E2=80=99s Workflow: Never leaving Chrome DevTools
http://remysharp.com/2012/12/21/my-workflow-never-having-to-leave-devtools=
/


--- Code and Libraries ---

# Sparky.js: Client-Side Application Scaffold
http://sparkyjs.com/

Sparky.js is a client-side application scaffold which helps those who want=
 to have organized structure in their app, but don't want to subscribe to=
 a particular client-side MVC framework.

# Motio: jQuery Plugin for Sprite-Based Animations and Panning
http://darsa.in/motio/

# Fay Programming Language: Subset of Haskell
http://fay-lang.org/

The Fay programming language is a subset of Haskell and includes features=
 such as static typing, lazy evaluation, purity by default. Fay is compile=
d to JavaScript.

# controldeck.js: Control HTML5 Presentations with Node.js
http://dfcb.github.com/controldeck.js/

Use case: remotely control your presentation from a mobile device.

# doT.js: Fast Template Engine
https://github.com/olado/doT

A fast and concise JavaScript template engine for Node.js and browsers. It=
 supports partials, custom delimiters and more.

# jQuery.Shapeshift: Dynamic Grid System with Drag and Drop Functionality
http://mcpants.github.com/jquery.shapeshift/

# setImmediate: Cross-Browser Implementation
https://github.com/NobleJS/setImmediate

This library shims setImmediate on various platforms. Quote: =E2=80=9CsetI=
mmediate allows scripts to yield to the browser, executing a given operati=
on asynchronously, in a manner that is typically more efficient and consum=
es less power than the usual setTimeout(..., 0) pattern.=E2=80=9D

# MD5-Password-Cracker.js: Crack MD5 Passwords with JavaScript Web Workers
https://github.com/feross/md5-password-cracker.js

# Numeral.js: Format and Manipulate Numbers
https://github.com/adamwdraper/Numeral-js

# Dojorama: Single-Page Demo Application Based on Dojo, Twitter Bootstrap=
 and the History API
https://github.com/sirprize/dojorama

# GruntStart: Grunt-Enabled Head-Start with H5BP, jQuery, Modernizr and Re=
spond
https://github.com/tsvensen/gruntstart

Building blocks to quickly get started with Grunt to create an optimized w=
ebsite.

# dfatool.js: Data Flow Analysis Tool for JavaScript Code
https://github.com/pissang/dfatool

What variables are defined in a given scope? What value does a variable ha=
ve at a given program location? Etc. Written in JavaScript, runs on Node.j=
s.

# jKit: jQuery-based User Interface Toolkit
http://jquery-jkit.com/commands/gallery.html

# PhantomJS 1.8 =E2=80=9CBlue Winter Rose=E2=80=9D Released
http://ariya.ofilabs.com/2012/12/phantomjs-1-8-blue-winter-rose.html


--- Watching ---

# Talks To Help You Become A Better Front-End Engineer In 2013
http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/12/22/talks-to-help-you-become-a-bett=
er-front-end-engineer-in-2013/

Addy Osmani unearths a large collection of talks about front-end developme=
nt topics. Mostly slide decks but some with video too.

# Top 20 Web Conference Talks of 2012
http://www.netmagazine.com/features/top-20-web-conference-talks-2012

# Web Components: An Introduction
http://vimeo.com/48054442

Web Components, in concert with the Shadow DOM, enable the encapsulation o=
f HTML5 user interface elements (video players, social buttons, etc.). Thi=
s video by T.J. Holowaychuk gives an introduction. Additionally, you can w=
atch the following two talks from JSConf EU 2012: Divya Manian: Web Compon=
ents and Angelina Fabbro: Inspector Web and the Mystery of the Shadow DOM


